<h1 id="guided_activities">Guided Activities</h1>
<span><p>
A guided activity is a series of experiments that explore a set of related ideas.
While these activity guides are written in the form of "teacher notes" they can also be used as
self-guided tutorials by motivated learners.
</p></span>

<ul class="list">
    <li><a href="cards/tn_Getting_Started.pdf">Getting Started with MicroBlocks</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/tn_Color_Mixing.pdf">Color Mixing</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/tn_Exploring_Electricity.pdf">Exploring Electricity</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/tn_micro_bit_dance.pdf">Make a micro:bit Dance</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/tn_Time_Scales.pdf">Time Scales</a></li>
</ul>

